Environment: Next.js 15 App Router app at meavo.app — the Meavo company tools dashboard and the **source of truth for identity** (users, teams, tool cards, access). NOT a satellite app.

## Stack

- Next.js 15+ (App Router), TypeScript strict, React 19
- Tailwind CSS 3 — in-house UI kit in `src/components/ui.tsx`, no external component libraries
- Prisma 6 via `@meavo/db` (shared Neon Postgres; schema lives in the meavo-db repo)
- NextAuth v5, JWT sessions — Credentials (bcryptjs) + invite-only Google
- Vercel hosting; Vercel Blob (HR PDFs, library assets); Resend email; Google Sheets import; Slack webhook digest

## Do NOT

- Edit the Prisma schema in this repo — schema lives in [meavo-db](https://github.com/meavo-booths/meavo-db); `npm run db:push` is intentionally disabled
- Run `prisma db push` with a stale schema — it can drop other apps' tables (one DB shared by all Meavo apps)
- Send email from anywhere except the notifications processor (`src/lib/notifications/`) — all sends go through the outbox + cron
- Import Prisma-backed auth in `src/middleware.ts` (edge) — middleware uses `src/lib/auth.config.ts` only
- Add REST endpoints for mutations — use Server Actions in `src/app/actions/`; API routes are for cron, health, auth, and file streaming only
- Look up tool cards by `linkedAppKey` at runtime — use stable `defaultCardId` from `src/lib/tool-card-registry.ts`
- Allow non-HTTPS tool card URLs
- Commit secrets or `.env*` files; document env var names in `.env.example` only

## Code layout

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Pages (authenticated) | `src/app/(app)/` — home, `admin/`, `hr/`, `library/`, `profile/` |
| Server Actions | `src/app/actions/` |
| API routes (cron/health/auth/streaming) | `src/app/api/` |
| Domain logic + integrations | `src/lib/` (flat modules), `src/lib/notifications/` |
| Auth | `src/lib/auth.ts`, `src/lib/auth.config.ts`, `src/middleware.ts` |
| UI kit + feature components | `src/components/` (`ui.tsx`, `modal.tsx`) |
| Targeted SQL migrations + seeds | `scripts/` |
| Tests | N/A — no test suite; verify manually |

## Data flow

```
Browser → Server Component page → Server Action (src/app/actions/)
        → Prisma (@meavo/db → shared Neon Postgres)
        → side effects: NotificationOutbox enqueue → cron → Resend
                        Vercel Blob (uploads) / Google Sheets (import cron) / Slack (digest cron)
```

Every mutation that should email someone must enqueue via `src/lib/notifications/enqueue.ts` (fire-and-forget with `.catch(console.error)`), never send directly. Call `revalidatePath()` after writes.

